    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.96,
      "end": 28.22,
      "text": "The Lamp.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 29.62,
      "end": 31.86,
      "text": "A lamp, well filled with oil,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 32.48,
      "end": 34.4,
      "text": "burned with a clear and steady light,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 34.98,
      "end": 39.54,
      "text": "and began to swell with pride and boasted Sean more brightly than the sun himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 40.52,
      "end": 43.94,
      "text": "Just then, a puff of wind came and blew it out.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 45.12,
      "end": 48.16,
      "text": "Someone struck a match and lit it again and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 49.0,
      "end": 51.52,
      "text": "You just keep a light, never mind the sun.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 52.16,
      "end": 56.2,
      "text": "Why, even the stars never need to be relit as you had to be just now.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 56.2,
      "end": 60.28,
      "text": "And of the lamp.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
